I just understood what was your proposition.
At first, I thought it was just copy/paste of common helpers from common/common/templates.
But actually, you also changed them.

As the change is relevant and not only for you IMHO, do you think it would be doable to push it in the common templates (of course we shouldn't change their use in other cases, that's where I'm not sure).

If it's not possible, I would prefer something like:


{{- define "common.labelsExtended" -}}
{{- $dot := default . .dot -}}
{{- $labels := default (dict) .labels -}}
{{ include "common.labels" .dot }}
{{- range $key, $val := $labels }}
{{printf "%s: %s" $key $val}}
{{ end -}}
{{- end -}}


Same for matchLabel, resourceMetadata, selectors, ...

And also, instead of creating your own file, readd them in common/common/templates/_labels.tpl.
